<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <title><%= title %></title>
    <meta name="csrf-token" content="<%= csrfToken %>">
    <%- include('../partials/head-assets') %>
    <script src="/js/theme-toggle.js" defer></script>
    <script src="/js/locator-repair-module.js" defer></script>
</head>

<body class="<%= (user && user.preferences && user.preferences.nightMode) ? 'dark-mode' : '' %>">
    <%- include('../partials/theme-toggle') %>
    <div
        class="container mt-5 mb-5"
        id="locator-repair-module-root"
        data-locator-repair-overview-endpoint="/api/locator-repair/overview"
        data-locator-repair-suggest-endpoint="/api/locator-repair/suggest"
        data-locator-repair-history-endpoint="/api/locator-repair/history"
        data-locator-repair-feedback-endpoint="/api/locator-repair/feedback"
        data-locator-repair-train-endpoint="/api/locator-repair/train">
        <div class="d-flex justify-content-between align-items-center mb-4 flex-wrap gap-3">
            <div>
                <h1 class="notes-title mb-1">Self-Healing Locator Repair Module</h1>
                <p class="text-muted mb-2">A research workspace for repairing broken Playwright and Selenium locators with trained, reviewable suggestions and deterministic self-heal gating.</p>
                <p class="text-muted mb-0">Paste a failed locator and the current DOM fragment, compare stable replacement strategies, then capture accept or reject feedback so the reranker improves over time.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="d-flex gap-2 flex-wrap">
                <a href="/research" class="btn btn-outline-dark">Back to Research</a>
                <a href="/playwright/module" class="btn btn-outline-dark">Open Playwright Testing Module</a>
                <a href="/selenium/module" class="btn btn-outline-dark">Open Selenium Testing Module</a>
                <a href="/notes" class="btn btn-secondary">Back to Notes</a>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="row g-3 mb-4">
            <div class="col-md-6 col-xl-3">
                <div class="card research-summary-card h-100">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <p class="research-kicker mb-2">Engine</p>
                        <p class="playwright-runtime-label mb-1" id="locator-repair-runtime-label">ML-assisted self-healing</p>
                        <p class="text-muted mb-0">Current ranking mode for self-healing suggestions.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6 col-xl-2">
                <div class="card research-summary-card h-100">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <p class="research-kicker mb-2">Samples</p>
                        <p class="display-6 mb-1" id="locator-repair-sample-count">0</p>
                        <p class="text-muted mb-0">App-shaped failure cases ready to load into the analyzer.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6 col-xl-2">
                <div class="card research-summary-card h-100">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <p class="research-kicker mb-2">Locator Families</p>
                        <p class="display-6 mb-1" id="locator-repair-family-count">0</p>
                        <p class="text-muted mb-0">Broken locator patterns the module can interpret today.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6 col-xl-2">
                <div class="card research-summary-card h-100">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <p class="research-kicker mb-2">Feedback</p>
                        <p class="display-6 mb-1" id="locator-repair-feedback-count">0</p>
                        <p class="text-muted mb-0">Accepted, rejected, and healed repair outcomes captured so far.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6 col-xl-2">
                <div class="card research-summary-card h-100">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <p class="research-kicker mb-2">Verified Heals</p>
                        <p class="display-6 mb-1" id="locator-repair-healed-count">0</p>
                        <p class="text-muted mb-0">Repairs that were trusted only after a deterministic verification step.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6 col-xl-3">
                <div class="card research-summary-card h-100">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <p class="research-kicker mb-2">Outputs</p>
                        <p class="display-6 mb-1 fs-4" id="locator-repair-output-targets">Playwright + Selenium</p>
                        <p class="text-muted mb-0">Every repair suggestion is rendered for both browser stacks.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card automation-card mb-4">
            <div class="card-body d-flex flex-column flex-xl-row justify-content-between align-items-xl-center gap-3">
                <div>
                    <h2 class="h5 mb-1">Self-Healing Controls</h2>
                    <p class="text-muted mb-1">Load a sample case, inspect the current repair ladder, then rank replacement locators from the supplied DOM snippet.</p>
                    <p class="text-muted small mb-0">Self-healing is allowed only when the trained reranker is confident and the healed locator still passes a deterministic follow-up check.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="d-flex gap-2 flex-wrap align-items-center">
                    <label for="locator-repair-sample-select" class="visually-hidden">Sample case</label>
                    <select id="locator-repair-sample-select" class="form-select">
                        <option value="">Loading samples...</option>
                    </select>
                    <button type="button" id="locator-repair-load-sample-btn" class="btn btn-outline-dark">Load Sample</button>
                    <button type="button" id="locator-repair-analyze-btn" class="btn btn-dark">Suggest Repairs</button>
                    <button type="button" id="locator-repair-train-btn" class="btn btn-outline-primary">Train Model</button>
                    <button type="button" id="locator-repair-refresh-history-btn" class="btn btn-outline-secondary">Refresh History</button>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="card-body pt-0">
                <div class="mb-3">
                    <h3 class="h6 mb-2">Control Guide</h3>
                    <p class="text-muted small mb-2">Each control explains how it contributes to the repair workflow.</p>
                    <div id="locator-repair-controls-guide" class="row g-3"></div>
                </div>
                <div id="locator-repair-status"></div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="row g-4 mb-4">
            <div class="col-xl-6">
                <div class="card automation-card h-100">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <span class="research-kicker">Process</span>
                        <h2 class="h4 mt-2 mb-1">Repair Workflow</h2>
                        <p class="text-muted small mb-3">Use the workflow as a repeatable path from a broken selector to a verified repair.</p>
                        <div id="locator-repair-workflow-grid" class="d-flex flex-column gap-3"></div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-xl-6">
                <div class="card automation-card h-100">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <span class="research-kicker">Strategy</span>
                        <h2 class="h4 mt-2 mb-1">Repair Ladder</h2>
                        <p class="text-muted small mb-3">The ranking engine prefers stable automation signals before it falls back to copy or structural guesses.</p>
                        <div id="locator-repair-ladder-grid" class="d-flex flex-column gap-3"></div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="row g-4 mb-4">
            <div class="col-xl-6">
                <div class="card automation-card h-100">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <span class="research-kicker">Model</span>
                        <h2 class="h4 mt-2 mb-1">Reranker State</h2>
                        <p class="text-muted small mb-3">The module uses a logistic reranker trained from bootstrap samples plus captured repair feedback.</p>
                        <div id="locator-repair-model-summary"></div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-xl-6">
                <div class="card automation-card h-100">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <span class="research-kicker">History</span>
                        <h2 class="h4 mt-2 mb-1">Recent Repair Outcomes</h2>
                        <p class="text-muted small mb-3">Accepted, rejected, and healed repairs become future training signal for the reranker.</p>
                        <div id="locator-repair-history-summary" class="mb-3"></div>
                        <div id="locator-repair-history-grid" class="d-flex flex-column gap-3"></div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="row g-4 mb-4">
            <div class="col-xl-6">
                <div class="card automation-card h-100">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <span class="research-kicker">Signals</span>
                        <h2 class="h4 mt-2 mb-1">Supported Signals</h2>
                        <p class="text-muted small mb-3">These are the attributes and intent clues the current engine can detect and rank.</p>
                        <div id="locator-repair-signals-grid" class="row g-3"></div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-xl-6">
                <div class="card automation-card h-100">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <span class="research-kicker">Examples</span>
                        <h2 class="h4 mt-2 mb-1">Sample Cases</h2>
                        <p class="text-muted small mb-3">These examples are grounded in this app’s Research, ML, Playwright, and auth flows.</p>
                        <div id="locator-repair-sample-grid" class="row g-3"></div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card automation-card mb-4">
            <div class="card-body">
                <span class="research-kicker">Analyzer</span>
                <h2 class="h4 mt-2 mb-1">Repair Input</h2>
                <p class="text-muted small mb-3">Paste the broken locator, explain the step’s intent, and provide the current DOM snippet around the intended element.</p>
                <form id="locator-repair-form" class="row g-3">
                    <div class="col-12">
                        <label for="locator-repair-original-locator" class="form-label">Original locator</label>
                        <input
                            type="text"
                            class="form-control"
                            id="locator-repair-original-locator"
                            placeholder='Examples: By.linkText("Open Alert Triage ML Module") or page.getByRole("button", { name: "Load Spec" })'>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-12">
                        <label for="locator-repair-step-goal" class="form-label">Step goal</label>
                        <input
                            type="text"
                            class="form-control"
                            id="locator-repair-step-goal"
                            placeholder="Describe the user intent, such as opening the Alert Triage ML Module or filling the email field.">
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-12">
                        <label for="locator-repair-html-snippet" class="form-label">Current HTML snippet</label>
                        <textarea
                            class="form-control"
                            id="locator-repair-html-snippet"
                            rows="12"
                            spellcheck="false"
                            placeholder="Paste the current DOM fragment around the intended element."></textarea>
                    </div>
                </form>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="row g-4">
            <div class="col-xl-4">
                <div class="card automation-card h-100">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <span class="research-kicker">Analysis</span>
                        <h2 class="h4 mt-2 mb-1">Signal Summary</h2>
                        <p class="text-muted small mb-3">Shows what the engine extracted from the original locator and what it thinks is risky.</p>
                        <div id="locator-repair-analysis-summary"></div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-xl-8">
                <div class="card automation-card h-100">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <div class="d-flex justify-content-between align-items-center gap-3 mb-3 flex-wrap">
                            <div>
                                <span class="research-kicker">Suggestions</span>
                                <h2 class="h4 mt-2 mb-1">Repair Candidates</h2>
                                <p class="text-muted mb-0">Review the ranked Playwright and Selenium replacements, then capture feedback so the reranker improves.</p>
                            </div>
                            <span class="badge text-bg-light" id="locator-repair-engine-badge">Waiting for analysis</span>
                        </div>
                        <div id="locator-repair-suggestions"></div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>

</html>
